SIMPLE: sea_horse
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sea horse
<hw>Sea" horse`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>A fabulous creature,
half horse and half fish, represented in classic mythology as driven by
sea dogs or ridden by the Nereids. It is also depicted in heraldry. See
<er>Hippocampus</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The walrus.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any fish of the genus Hippocampus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In a passage of Dryden's, the word is supposed to refer
to the hippopotamus.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea hulver</ent>⟦br⟧
